<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>{{ symbol }} — Fundamentals Deep Dive</title>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@4.4.1/dist/chart.umd.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chartjs-plugin-annotation@3.0.1/dist/chartjs-plugin-annotation.min.js"></script>
<style>
:root{--bg:#0f1117;--card:#1a1d28;--border:#2a2d3a;--text:#e4e4e7;--dim:#71717a;--green:#22c55e;--red:#ef4444;--blue:#3b82f6;--yellow:#eab308;--cyan:#06b6d4;--purple:#a855f7;--orange:#f97316}
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Inter',sans-serif;line-height:1.6;padding:2rem}
.container{max-width:1400px;margin:0 auto}h1{font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:0.25rem}.subtitle{color:var(--dim);margin-bottom:2rem;font-size:0.9rem}
.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-bottom:2rem}.grid-3{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-bottom:2rem}
.card{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem}.card h2{font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--cyan);margin-bottom:0.8rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding-bottom:0.5rem}
.full-width{grid-column:1/-1}table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:0.82rem}th{text-align:left;padding:0.35rem 0.5rem;color:var(--dim);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);font-weight:500}td{padding:0.35rem 0.5rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
th.r,td.r{text-align:right}tr:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03)}.up{color:var(--green)}.down{color:var(--red)}.hl{color:var(--cyan);font-weight:600}
.badge{display:inline-block;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:600}.bg{background:rgba(34,197,94,0.15);color:var(--green)}.br{background:rgba(239,68,68,0.15);color:var(--red)}.by{background:rgba(234,179,8,0.15);color:var(--yellow)}
.stat-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(6,1fr);gap:0.8rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem}.stat{text-align:center}.stat-value{font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700}.stat-label{font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--dim)}
.narrative{background:rgba(6,182,212,0.05);border-left:3px solid var(--cyan);padding:1rem;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:1rem 0;font-size:0.85rem}.narrative strong{color:var(--cyan)}
.explain{background:rgba(168,85,247,0.06);border-left:3px solid var(--purple);padding:0.8rem 1rem;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:0.6rem 0;font-size:0.82rem;color:#c4b5fd}
.explain strong{color:var(--purple)}
.example{background:rgba(234,179,8,0.06);border-left:3px solid var(--yellow);padding:0.8rem 1rem;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:0.6rem 0;font-size:0.82rem}
.example strong{color:var(--yellow)}
.callout{background:rgba(34,197,94,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3);border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin:1rem 0;font-size:0.85rem}
.callout-warn{background:rgba(239,68,68,0.08);border-color:rgba(239,68,68,0.3)}
.callout-neutral{background:rgba(234,179,8,0.08);border-color:rgba(234,179,8,0.3)}
.note{color:var(--dim);font-size:0.78rem;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:0.5rem}
.chart-box{position:relative;height:380px}
.cite{color:var(--dim);font-size:0.72rem;font-style:italic}
.source-tag{display:inline-block;background:rgba(6,182,212,0.1);color:var(--cyan);padding:1px 6px;border-radius:3px;font-size:0.7rem;margin-left:4px}
.term{color:var(--purple);font-weight:600;cursor:help;border-bottom:1px dotted var(--purple)}
.chart-toggle{display:inline-block;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.78rem;cursor:pointer;border:1px solid var(--border);background:transparent;color:var(--dim);margin:0 2px;transition:all 0.15s}
.chart-toggle:hover{border-color:var(--cyan);color:var(--text)}
.chart-toggle.active{background:var(--cyan);color:var(--bg);border-color:var(--cyan);font-weight:600}
.toggle-bar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:4px;margin-bottom:1rem;align-items:center}
@media(max-width:768px){.grid,.grid-3{grid-template-columns:1fr}.stat-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr)}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

{# ============ SECTION 1: HEADER ============ #}
<h1>{{ symbol }} <span style="color:var(--dim);font-weight:400;font-size:1.1rem">Fundamentals & Valuation</span></h1>
<p class="subtitle">{{ industry }} | Market Cap ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(mcap_cr) }} Cr | Data: yfinance + Screener.in + BSE Concalls | {{ report_date }}</p>

{# ============ SECTION 2: KEY STATS BAR ============ #}
<div class="stat-grid">
<div class="stat"><div class="stat-value">₹{{ "{:,.1f}".format(price) }}</div><div class="stat-label">CMP (Current Market Price)</div></div>
<div class="stat"><div class="stat-value" style="color:var(--green)">{{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing or 0) }}x</div><div class="stat-label">P/E{% if pe_percentile is not none %} — {% if pe_percentile == 0 %}All-Time Low{% else %}{{ "%.0f"|format(pe_percentile) }}th %ile{% endif %}{% endif %}</div></div>
<div class="stat"><div class="stat-value {% if v.earnings_growth and v.earnings_growth > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.1f"|format((v.earnings_growth or 0) * 100) }}%</div><div class="stat-label">Earnings Growth (last 12 months)</div></div>
<div class="stat"><div class="stat-value">{{ "%.2f"|format(v.beta or 0) }}</div><div class="stat-label">Beta (low = less volatile)</div></div>
<div class="stat"><div class="stat-value up">{{ roce }}%</div><div class="stat-label">ROCE (latest FY)</div></div>
<div class="stat"><div class="stat-value up">+{{ upside_pct }}%</div><div class="stat-label">Analyst Upside ({{ num_analysts }} analysts)</div></div>
</div>

{# ============ SECTION 3: GLOSSARY ============ #}
<div class="card" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Financial Terms Used in This Report — Plain English Guide</h2>
<p class="note">Every term you'll see below, explained with {{ symbol }}'s actual numbers as examples.</p>
<table>
<tr><td class="hl" style="width:140px">CMP</td><td><strong>Current Market Price</strong> — what one share costs right now on the stock exchange. {{ symbol }}'s CMP is ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(price) }}. This changes every second during market hours.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">Market Cap</td><td><strong>Market Capitalization</strong> — the total value of ALL shares of the company. CMP × Total Shares = ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(price) }} × {{ "%.1f"|format(shares / 1e7) }} Cr shares = ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(mcap_cr) }} Cr. Think of it as "how much would it cost to buy the entire company?"</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">EPS</td><td><strong>Earnings Per Share</strong> — how much profit the company made for each share. Net Profit / Total Shares. {{ symbol }} earned ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(ni_annual) }} Cr in the last FY with {{ "%.1f"|format(shares / 1e7) }} Cr shares, so EPS = ~₹{{ eps_annual }}/share.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">P/E Ratio</td><td><strong>Price-to-Earnings</strong> — how many years of current earnings you're paying for. CMP / EPS. {{ symbol }}: ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(price) }} / ₹{{ eps_annual }} = {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x. <em>Lower P/E = cheaper.</em></td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">ATL</td><td><strong>All-Time Low</strong> — the lowest value this metric has ever reached in the stock's history.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">EV/EBITDA</td><td><strong>Enterprise Value / EBITDA</strong>. EV = Market Cap + Debt - Cash. Better than P/E because it adjusts for cash/debt on the balance sheet.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">EBITDA</td><td><strong>Earnings Before Interest, Tax, Depreciation & Amortisation</strong> — how much cash the core business generates before accounting items.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">Gross Margin</td><td>% of revenue left after direct costs. Higher = better pricing power.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">OPM</td><td><strong>Operating Profit Margin</strong> — % of revenue left after ALL operating costs. Best measure of core business profitability.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">Net Margin</td><td>Final % left after everything — costs, interest, taxes, other income.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">ROCE</td><td><strong>Return on Capital Employed</strong> — Operating Profit / Capital Employed. Above 20% is excellent. {{ symbol }}'s {{ roce }}% means every ₹100 of capital generates ₹{{ roce }} of operating profit.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">D/E Ratio</td><td><strong>Debt-to-Equity</strong> — how leveraged the company is. {{ symbol }}'s {{ "%.3f"|format(v.debt_to_equity or 0) }} means virtually zero debt. Below 0.5 = conservative, above 1 = aggressive.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">Current Ratio</td><td>Current Assets / Current Liabilities. Above 1.5 = comfortable. {{ symbol }}: {{ "%.2f"|format(v.current_ratio or 0) }}x.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">OCF / CFO</td><td><strong>Operating Cash Flow</strong> — actual cash generated by the business. When OCF > Net Profit, earnings are "real."</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">Beta</td><td>Stock's sensitivity to market moves. {{ symbol }}'s {{ "%.2f"|format(v.beta or 0) }} means if Nifty falls 10%, {{ symbol }} typically falls only {{ "%.0f"|format((v.beta or 0) * 10) }}%.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">Deferred Revenue</td><td>Cash collected but not yet recognized as revenue. High growth in deferred revenue = future revenue already locked in.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">BVPS</td><td><strong>Book Value Per Share</strong> — net assets / shares. {{ symbol }}: ₹{{ "%.0f"|format(v.book_value_per_share or 0) }}. Stock at ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(price) }} = {{ "%.1f"|format(price / (v.book_value_per_share or 1)) }}x book value.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="hl">Working Capital Days</td><td>How many days of revenue are tied up in operations. Negative = customers fund the business (subscription model).</td></tr>
</table>
</div>

{# ============ SECTION 4: VALUATION CALLOUT ============ #}
{% if pe_percentile is not none and pe_percentile <= 10 %}
<div class="callout" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<strong style="color:var(--green);font-size:1rem">This Stock is at Its Cheapest-Ever Valuation</strong><br><br>
<div class="explain">
<strong>What does "cheapest ever" mean?</strong> P/E is {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x today. Over {{ pe_observations }} weekly observations since {{ pe_period_start }}, the P/E ranged from {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x (now) to {{ "%.0f"|format(pe_band.max_val or 0) }}x. The median was {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_median) }}x. Today's {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x is at the {{ "%.0f"|format(pe_percentile) }}th percentile.
</div>
<div class="example">
<strong>In rupees:</strong> At the median P/E of {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_median) }}x and current EPS of ~₹{{ eps_annual }}, the stock "should" trade at {{ "%.0f"|format(pe_median * eps_annual) }}. It trades at ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(price) }} — a {{ "%.0f"|format((1 - price / (pe_median * eps_annual)) * 100) }}% discount to its historical median valuation.
</div>
</div>
{% elif pe_percentile is not none and pe_percentile <= 30 %}
<div class="callout-neutral" style="border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin:1rem 0 2rem;font-size:0.85rem">
<strong style="color:var(--yellow);font-size:1rem">Trading Below Historical Average</strong><br><br>
P/E of {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x is at the {{ "%.0f"|format(pe_percentile) }}th percentile — cheaper than {{ "%.0f"|format(100 - pe_percentile) }}% of historical observations. Median P/E: {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_median) }}x.
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 5: UNIFIED CHART with METRIC TOGGLES ============ #}
{% if screener_charts or (price_chart and price_chart.dates) %}
<div class="card full-width" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Charts</h2>
<div class="toggle-bar" id="metricToggles">
<button class="chart-toggle active" onclick="switchChart('price', this)">Price</button>
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="switchChart('pe', this)">PE Ratio</button>
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="switchChart('margins', this)">Sales &amp; Margin</button>
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="switchChart('ev_ebitda', this)">EV / EBITDA</button>
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="switchChart('pb', this)">Price to Book</button>
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="switchChart('mcap_sales', this)">Market Cap / Sales</button>
</div>
<div class="chart-box" style="height:400px"><canvas id="mainChart"></canvas></div>
<div id="chartExplain" class="explain" style="margin-top:0.8rem"></div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 8: COMPOUNDED GROWTH RATES ============ #}
{% if growth_rates %}
<div class="card full-width" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Compounded Growth Rates</h2>
<p class="note">How fast has the company been growing? These are annualised (CAGR) rates.</p>
<div class="grid" style="gap:1rem">
<table>
<thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th class="r">10Y</th><th class="r">5Y</th><th class="r">3Y</th><th class="r">TTM</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Sales Growth</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.sales_10y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.sales_10y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.sales_10y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.sales_5y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.sales_5y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.sales_5y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.sales_3y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.sales_3y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.sales_3y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.sales_ttm is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.sales_ttm > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.sales_ttm * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
</tr>
<tr><td>Profit Growth</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.profit_10y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.profit_10y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.profit_10y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.profit_5y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.profit_5y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.profit_5y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.profit_3y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.profit_3y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.profit_3y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.profit_ttm is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.profit_ttm > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.profit_ttm * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
</tr>
<tr><td>Stock Price CAGR</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.price_10y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.price_10y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.price_10y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.price_5y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.price_5y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.price_5y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.price_3y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.price_3y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.price_3y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.price_1y is not none %}<span class="{% if growth_rates.price_1y > 0 %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.price_1y * 100) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
</tr>
<tr><td>Avg ROE</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.roe_10y is not none %}{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.roe_10y * 100) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.roe_5y is not none %}{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.roe_5y * 100) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.roe_3y is not none %}{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.roe_3y * 100) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
<td class="r">{% if growth_rates.roe_last is not none and growth_rates.roe_last is defined %}{{ "%.0f"|format(growth_rates.roe_last * 100) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<div>
<div class="explain">
<strong>What is CAGR?</strong> Compounded Annual Growth Rate — the steady annual rate at which something grew. Example: if sales grew from ₹100 Cr to ₹200 Cr in 5 years, CAGR = 15% (not 100%/5 = 20%). CAGR accounts for compounding.<br><br>
<strong>How to read:</strong> Sales CAGR of 20%+ over 5-10 years = strong secular growth. Profit growing faster than sales = improving margins. Stock price lagging profit growth = potential re-rating opportunity.
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 9: THREE CARDS — VALUATION / PROFITABILITY / BALANCE SHEET ============ #}
<div class="grid-3">

{# VALUATION CARD #}
<div class="card">
<h2>Valuation Multiples</h2>
<p class="note">These answer: "Is the stock cheap or expensive?"</p>
<table>
<tr><td>P/E Trailing</td><td class="r"><strong class="{% if pe_percentile is not none and pe_percentile <= 20 %}up{% endif %}">{{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x</strong>{% if pe_percentile is not none and pe_percentile == 0 %} <span class="badge bg">ATL</span>{% endif %}</td></tr>
<tr><td>P/E Forward</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(pe_forward or 0) }}x</td></tr>
<tr><td>P/B</td><td class="r">{{ "%.2f"|format(v.pb_ratio or 0) }}x</td></tr>
<tr><td>EV/EBITDA</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(v.ev_ebitda or 0) }}x</td></tr>
<tr><td>EV/Revenue</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(v.ev_revenue or 0) }}x</td></tr>
<tr><td>P/Sales</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(v.ps_ratio or 0) }}x</td></tr>
<tr><td>Dividend Yield</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(v.dividend_yield or 0) }}%</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="explain">
<strong>P/E of {{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x</strong> means you pay ₹{{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }} for every ₹1 of annual earnings.
<strong>EV/EBITDA of {{ "%.1f"|format(v.ev_ebitda or 0) }}x</strong> adjusts for the company's cash pile — often a better measure than P/E.
</div>
</div>

{# PROFITABILITY CARD #}
<div class="card">
<h2>Profitability</h2>
<p class="note">These answer: "How good is this business?"</p>
<table>
<tr><td>Gross Margin</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format((v.gross_margin or 0) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
<tr><td>Operating Margin</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format((v.operating_margin or 0) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
<tr><td>Net Margin</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format((v.net_margin or 0) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
<tr><td>Revenue Growth</td><td class="r {% if v.revenue_growth and v.revenue_growth > 0 %}up{% endif %}">+{{ "%.1f"|format((v.revenue_growth or 0) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
<tr><td>Earnings Growth</td><td class="r {% if v.earnings_growth and v.earnings_growth > 0 %}up{% endif %}">+{{ "%.1f"|format((v.earnings_growth or 0) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
<tr><td>ROCE (latest FY)</td><td class="r up">{{ roce }}%</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="explain">
<strong>Margins as a waterfall:</strong><br>
₹100 Revenue → ₹{{ "%.0f"|format((v.gross_margin or 0) * 100) }} Gross Profit ({{ "%.1f"|format((v.gross_margin or 0) * 100) }}%) → ₹{{ "%.0f"|format((v.operating_margin or 0) * 100) }} Operating Profit ({{ "%.1f"|format((v.operating_margin or 0) * 100) }}%) → ₹{{ "%.0f"|format((v.net_margin or 0) * 100) }} Net Profit ({{ "%.1f"|format((v.net_margin or 0) * 100) }}%)
</div>
</div>

{# BALANCE SHEET CARD #}
<div class="card">
<h2>Balance Sheet & Liquidity</h2>
<p class="note">These answer: "Is this company financially safe?"</p>
{% set total_cash = v.total_cash or 0 %}
{% set total_debt = v.total_debt or 0 %}
{% set net_cash = total_cash - total_debt %}
<table>
<tr><td>D/E Ratio</td><td class="r"><strong class="{% if (v.debt_to_equity or 0) < 0.1 %}up{% endif %}">{{ "%.3f"|format(v.debt_to_equity or 0) }}</strong>{% if (v.debt_to_equity or 0) < 0.05 %} <span class="badge bg">Near Zero</span>{% endif %}</td></tr>
<tr><td>Current Ratio</td><td class="r">{{ "%.2f"|format(v.current_ratio or 0) }}x</td></tr>
<tr><td>Total Cash</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(total_cash / 1e7) }} Cr</td></tr>
<tr><td>Total Debt</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(total_debt / 1e7) }} Cr</td></tr>
<tr><td>Net Cash</td><td class="r {% if net_cash > 0 %}up{% endif %}">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(net_cash / 1e7) }} Cr</td></tr>
<tr><td>BVPS</td><td class="r">₹{{ "%.0f"|format(v.book_value_per_share or 0) }}</td></tr>
<tr><td>Op Cash Flow</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format((v.operating_cash_flow or 0) / 1e7) }} Cr</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="explain">
<strong>Net Cash of ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(net_cash / 1e7) }} Cr</strong> = {{ "%.0f"|format(net_cash / 1e7 / mcap_cr * 100) }}% of market cap. If you bought the entire company, you'd get ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(net_cash / 1e7) }} Cr back from the bank account.<br><br>
<strong>OCF of ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format((v.operating_cash_flow or 0) / 1e7) }} Cr vs Net Profit ₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(ni_annual) }} Cr</strong> — {% if (v.operating_cash_flow or 0) / 1e7 > ni_annual %}earnings are backed by real cash (OCF > NI){% else %}OCF below net profit — worth investigating{% endif %}.
</div>
</div>
</div>

{# ============ SECTION 10: PRICE CONTEXT ============ #}
<div class="card" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Price Context</h2>
<table>
<tr><td>52-Week High</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(v.fifty_two_week_high or 0) }}</td><td>52-Week Low</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(v.fifty_two_week_low or 0) }}</td></tr>
<tr><td>Beta</td><td class="r">{{ "%.3f"|format(v.beta or 0) }}</td><td>Avg Volume</td><td class="r">{{ "{:,}".format(v.avg_volume or 0) }}</td></tr>
<tr><td>Shares Outstanding</td><td class="r">{{ "{:,}".format(v.shares_outstanding or 0) }}</td><td>Float</td><td class="r">{{ "{:,}".format(v.float_shares or 0) }}</td></tr>
{% if shareholding %}
<tr><td>Promoter Hold</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(shareholding.get('promoter', {}).get('pct', 0)) }}%</td><td>FII Hold</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(shareholding.get('fii', {}).get('pct', 0)) }}%</td></tr>
{% endif %}
</table>
</div>

{# ============ SECTION 11: ANALYST CONSENSUS ============ #}
{% if consensus %}
<div class="card" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Analyst Consensus & Scenario Analysis</h2>
<p class="note">Source: yfinance consensus from {{ consensus.num_analysts or 0 }} professional analysts.</p>
<table>
<tr><td>Target Mean</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(consensus.target_mean or 0) }}</td><td>Target Median</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(consensus.target_median or 0) }}</td></tr>
<tr><td>Target High</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(consensus.target_high or 0) }}</td><td>Target Low</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(consensus.target_low or 0) }}</td></tr>
<tr><td>Forward P/E</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(consensus.forward_pe or 0) }}x</td><td>Forward EPS</td><td class="r">₹{{ "%.1f"|format(consensus.forward_eps or 0) }}</td></tr>
<tr><td>Upside to Mean</td><td class="r up">+{{ upside_pct }}%</td><td>Earnings Growth</td><td class="r up">{{ "%.1f"|format((v.earnings_growth or 0) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
</table>
{% set fwd_eps = consensus.forward_eps or eps_annual %}
<h3 style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--dim)">Scenario Analysis — What Could the Stock Be Worth?</h3>
<table>
<thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th class="r">P/E</th><th class="r">EPS</th><th class="r">Target</th><th class="r">Upside</th></tr></thead>
<tr><td><span class="badge br">Bear</span> P/E stays at current</td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(pe_trailing) }}x</td><td class="r">₹{{ "%.0f"|format(fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(pe_trailing * fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r {% if pe_trailing * fwd_eps > price %}up{% else %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%.1f"|format((pe_trailing * fwd_eps / price - 1) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
<tr><td><span class="badge by">Base</span> Modest re-rating</td><td class="r">25x</td><td class="r">₹{{ "%.0f"|format(fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(25 * fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r up">+{{ "%.1f"|format((25 * fwd_eps / price - 1) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
<tr><td><span class="badge bg">Bull</span> Re-rating to 35x</td><td class="r">35x</td><td class="r">₹{{ "%.0f"|format(fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(35 * fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r up">+{{ "%.1f"|format((35 * fwd_eps / price - 1) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
{% if pe_median > 35 %}
<tr><td><span class="badge bg">Median reversion</span></td><td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(pe_median) }}x</td><td class="r">₹{{ "%.0f"|format(fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r">₹{{ "{:,.0f}".format(pe_median * fwd_eps) }}</td><td class="r up">+{{ "%.1f"|format((pe_median * fwd_eps / price - 1) * 100) }}%</td></tr>
{% endif %}
</table>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 12: QUARTERLY EARNINGS CHART ============ #}
{% if qr_chart.dates %}
<div class="card" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Quarterly Earnings — {{ qr_chart.dates|length }} Quarter Trend</h2>
<p class="note">Source: Screener.in. Revenue and Net Income in ₹Cr, OPM% on right axis.</p>
<div class="chart-box"><canvas id="qrChart"></canvas></div>
<div class="explain" style="margin-top:1rem">
<strong>How to read:</strong> Blue bars = Revenue (total earnings). Green bars = Net Income (final profit). Orange line = OPM (Operating Profit Margin — what % of revenue becomes operating profit).
</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 13: FULL QUARTERLY RESULTS TABLE ============ #}
{% if quarterly_full %}
<details style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<summary style="cursor:pointer;background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:12px;padding:1rem 1.5rem;font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--cyan);font-weight:600">
Full Quarterly Results — {{ quarterly_full|length }} Quarters (click to expand)
</summary>
<div class="card" style="border-top:none;border-radius:0 0 12px 12px;overflow-x:auto">
<p class="note">Source: Screener.in. All values in ₹Cr except EPS (₹) and margins (%).</p>
<table style="font-size:0.78rem">
<thead><tr><th>Metric</th>{% for q in quarterly_full %}<th class="r">{{ q.quarter_end[:7] }}</th>{% endfor %}</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for label, key, fmt in [('Sales', 'revenue', ',.0f'), ('Expenses', 'expenses', ',.0f'), ('Op Profit', 'operating_income', ',.0f'), ('OPM %', 'operating_margin', None), ('Other Income', 'other_income', ',.1f'), ('Interest', 'interest', ',.1f'), ('Depreciation', 'depreciation', ',.1f'), ('PBT', 'profit_before_tax', ',.1f'), ('Tax %', 'tax_pct', None), ('Net Income', 'net_income', ',.0f'), ('EPS', 'eps', ',.1f')] %}
<tr><td><strong>{{ label }}</strong></td>
{% for q in quarterly_full %}
<td class="r">{% if key == 'operating_margin' %}{% if q[key] is not none %}{{ "%.1f"|format(q[key] * 100) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}{% elif key == 'tax_pct' %}{% if q[key] is not none %}{{ "%.0f"|format(q[key]) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}{% elif q[key] is not none %}{{ ("{:" + fmt + "}").format(q[key]) }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
{% endfor %}
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="explain" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
<strong>Key rows:</strong> <em>Sales</em> = total revenue. <em>OPM %</em> = Operating Profit / Sales — measures core business profitability. <em>PBT</em> = Profit Before Tax. <em>Tax %</em> = effective tax rate. <em>Net Income</em> = final profit. Consistent OPM expansion quarter after quarter is a strong quality signal.
</div>
</div>
</details>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 14: ANNUAL FINANCIALS P&L+BS+CF ============ #}
{% if af_table %}
<div class="card full-width" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Annual Financials — {{ af_table|length }} Year Trend</h2>
<p class="note">Source: Screener.in. All values in ₹Cr except EPS (₹) and % rows.</p>
<table>
<thead><tr><th>Metric</th>{% for a in af_table %}<th class="r">FY{{ a.fiscal_year_end[:4] }}</th>{% endfor %}{% if ttm %}<th class="r" style="color:var(--cyan)">TTM</th>{% endif %}<th>Trend</th></tr></thead>
{% set ncols = af_table|length + 2 + (1 if ttm else 0) %}
<tbody>
{# — P&L Waterfall — #}
<tr><td colspan="{{ ncols }}" style="color:var(--cyan);font-weight:600;padding-top:0.5rem">Profit & Loss</td></tr>
{% for label, key, is_pct in [('Sales', 'revenue', false), ('Expenses', 'total_expenses', false), ('Operating Profit', 'operating_profit', false), ('OPM %', 'opm_pct', true), ('Other Income', 'other_income', false), ('Interest', 'interest', false), ('Depreciation', 'depreciation', false), ('Profit before tax', 'profit_before_tax', false), ('Tax %', 'tax_pct_annual', true), ('Net Profit', 'net_income', false), ('EPS in Rs', 'eps', false), ('Dividend Payout %', 'dividend_payout_pct', true)] %}
<tr{% if is_pct %} style="color:var(--dim)"{% endif %}><td>{{ label }}</td>{% for a in af_table %}<td class="r">{% if a[key] is not none %}{% if is_pct %}{{ "%.0f"|format(a[key]) }}%{% else %}{{ "%.1f"|format(a[key]) }}{% endif %}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>{% endfor %}{% if ttm %}<td class="r" style="color:var(--cyan)">{% if ttm[key] is defined and ttm[key] is not none %}{% if is_pct %}{{ "%.0f"|format(ttm[key]) }}%{% else %}{{ "%.1f"|format(ttm[key]) }}{% endif %}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>{% endif %}<td>{% set vals = af_table|map(attribute=key)|select('ne', none)|list %}{% if vals|length >= 2 and not is_pct %}{% if vals[-1] > vals[0] * 1.1 %}<span class="up">Improving</span>{% elif vals[-1] < vals[0] * 0.9 %}<span class="down">Declining</span>{% else %}Stable{% endif %}{% elif vals|length >= 2 and is_pct %}{% if vals[-1] > vals[0] + 2 %}<span class="up">Expanding</span>{% elif vals[-1] < vals[0] - 2 %}<span class="down">Contracting</span>{% else %}Stable{% endif %}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td></tr>
{% endfor %}
{# — Balance Sheet — #}
<tr><td colspan="{{ ncols }}" style="color:var(--cyan);font-weight:600;padding-top:0.5rem">Balance Sheet</td></tr>
{% for label, key in [('Equity Capital', 'equity_capital'), ('Reserves', 'reserves'), ('Borrowings', 'borrowings'), ('Total Assets', 'total_assets'), ('Cash & Bank', 'cash_and_bank')] %}
<tr><td>{{ label }}</td>{% for a in af_table %}<td class="r">{% if a[key] is not none %}{{ "%.1f"|format(a[key]) }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>{% endfor %}{% if ttm %}<td class="r">—</td>{% endif %}<td>{% set vals = af_table|map(attribute=key)|select('ne', none)|list %}{% if vals|length >= 2 %}{% if vals[-1] > vals[0] * 1.1 %}<span class="up">Improving</span>{% elif vals[-1] < vals[0] * 0.9 %}<span class="down">Declining</span>{% else %}Stable{% endif %}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td></tr>
{% endfor %}
{# — Cash Flow — #}
<tr><td colspan="{{ ncols }}" style="color:var(--cyan);font-weight:600;padding-top:0.5rem">Cash Flow</td></tr>
{% for label, key in [('CFO', 'cfo'), ('CFI', 'cfi'), ('CFF', 'cff'), ('Net Cash Flow', 'net_cash_flow')] %}
<tr><td>{{ label }}</td>{% for a in af_table %}<td class="r">{% if a[key] is not none %}{{ "%.1f"|format(a[key]) }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>{% endfor %}{% if ttm %}<td class="r">—</td>{% endif %}<td>{% set vals = af_table|map(attribute=key)|select('ne', none)|list %}{% if vals|length >= 2 %}{% if vals[-1] > vals[0] * 1.1 %}<span class="up">Improving</span>{% elif vals[-1] < vals[0] * 0.9 %}<span class="down">Declining</span>{% else %}Stable{% endif %}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td></tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 15: EFFICIENCY RATIOS ============ #}
{% if ratios_table %}
<div class="card full-width" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Efficiency Ratios — {{ ratios_table|length }} Year Trend</h2>
<p class="note">Source: Screener.in ratios section.</p>
<table>
<thead><tr><th>Metric</th>{% for r in ratios_table %}<th class="r">{{ r.fiscal_year_end[:4] }}</th>{% endfor %}</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for label, key in [('ROCE %', 'roce_pct'), ('Debtor Days', 'debtor_days'), ('Working Capital Days', 'working_capital_days'), ('Inventory Days', 'inventory_days'), ('Days Payable', 'days_payable'), ('Cash Conversion Cycle', 'cash_conversion_cycle')] %}
{% set all_none = ratios_table|map(attribute=key)|select('none')|list|length == ratios_table|length %}
{% if not all_none %}
<tr><td>{{ label }}</td>{% for r in ratios_table %}<td class="r">{% if r[key] is not none %}{{ "%.0f"|format(r[key]) }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>{% endfor %}</tr>
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 16: ROE HISTORY ============ #}
{% if roe_history and roe_history|selectattr('roe')|list %}
<div class="card full-width" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>ROE History — Return on Equity</h2>
<p class="note">ROE = Net Income / Shareholder Equity. Measures how efficiently the company uses shareholder money.</p>
<div class="chart-box" style="height:280px"><canvas id="roeChart"></canvas></div>
<div class="explain" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
<strong>What is ROE?</strong> If shareholders have ₹100 invested in the company and it earns ₹20 profit, ROE = 20%. Above 15% is good, above 20% is excellent. Consistently high ROE = the business is a compounding machine.<br><br>
<strong>ROE vs ROCE:</strong> ROCE measures returns on ALL capital (equity + debt). ROE measures returns only on shareholder equity. For low-debt companies like {{ symbol }}, they should be similar.
</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 17: SHAREHOLDING PATTERN with QUARTERLY/YEARLY TOGGLE ============ #}
{% if shareholding_history and shareholding_history|length >= 2 %}
<div class="card full-width" style="margin-bottom:2rem">
<h2>Shareholding Pattern — {{ shareholding_history|length }} Quarter History</h2>
<p class="note">Source: BSE quarterly filings. Shows % held by each category.</p>
{% set sh_cats = ['promoter', 'fii', 'dii', 'mf', 'insurance', 'public'] %}
{% set sh_labels = {'promoter': 'Promoter', 'fii': 'FII', 'dii': 'DII', 'mf': 'Mutual Funds', 'insurance': 'Insurance', 'public': 'Public', 'aif': 'AIF'} %}
{% set sh_reversed = shareholding_history | reverse | list %}

<div class="toggle-bar">
<button class="chart-toggle active" onclick="toggleShTab('quarterly', this)">Quarterly</button>
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="toggleShTab('yearly', this)">Yearly</button>
</div>

{# --- Quarterly Tab --- #}
<div id="sh-quarterly" style="display:block">
<div style="overflow-x:auto">
<table style="font-size:0.82rem">
<thead><tr><th>Category</th>{% for sh in sh_reversed %}<th class="r">{{ sh.quarter[:7] }}</th>{% endfor %}<th class="r">QoQ Chg</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for cat in sh_cats %}
{% set cat_vals = [] %}
{% for sh in sh_reversed %}{% if sh[cat] is defined %}{% set _ = cat_vals.append(sh[cat]) %}{% else %}{% set _ = cat_vals.append(0) %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}
<tr>
<td><strong>{{ sh_labels.get(cat, cat|title) }}</strong></td>
{% for val in cat_vals %}<td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(val) }}%</td>{% endfor %}
<td class="r">{% if cat_vals|length >= 2 %}{% set chg = cat_vals[-1] - cat_vals[-2] %}<span class="{% if chg > 0.05 %}up{% elif chg < -0.05 %}down{% endif %}">{{ "%+.1f"|format(chg) }}%</span>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class="chart-box" style="height:280px;margin-top:1rem"><canvas id="shChart"></canvas></div>
</div>

{# --- Yearly Tab (one entry per year — prefer March, else latest available) --- #}
<div id="sh-yearly" style="display:none">
{% set yearly_quarters = [] %}
{% set seen_years = [] %}
{% for sh in sh_reversed %}
{% set yr = sh.quarter[:4] %}
{% if yr not in seen_years %}{% set _ = seen_years.append(yr) %}{% set _ = yearly_quarters.append(sh) %}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
<div style="overflow-x:auto">
<table style="font-size:0.82rem">
<thead><tr><th>Category</th>{% for sh in yearly_quarters %}<th class="r">{{ sh.quarter[:7] }}</th>{% endfor %}</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for cat in sh_cats %}
{% set cat_vals = [] %}
{% for sh in yearly_quarters %}{% if sh[cat] is defined %}{% set _ = cat_vals.append(sh[cat]) %}{% else %}{% set _ = cat_vals.append(0) %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}
<tr>
<td><strong>{{ sh_labels.get(cat, cat|title) }}</strong></td>
{% for val in cat_vals %}<td class="r">{{ "%.1f"|format(val) }}%</td>{% endfor %}
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>

{# --- DII+ / FII+ expand buttons --- #}
<div style="margin-top:0.8rem">
{% if screener_shareholders and screener_shareholders.dii %}
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="toggleDetail('dii-detail', this)">DIIs+ ({{ screener_shareholders.dii|length }} schemes)</button>
{% endif %}
{% if screener_shareholders and screener_shareholders.fii %}
<button class="chart-toggle" onclick="toggleDetail('fii-detail', this)">FIIs+ ({{ screener_shareholders.fii|length }} funds)</button>
{% endif %}
</div>

{# --- DII detail table (hidden by default) --- #}
{% if screener_shareholders and screener_shareholders.dii %}
{% set dii = screener_shareholders.dii %}
{% set dii_q = screener_shareholders.dii_quarters %}
<div id="dii-detail" style="display:none;margin-top:1rem">
<h3 style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--cyan);margin-bottom:0.5rem">Mutual Fund Scheme Holdings — {{ dii|length }} Schemes</h3>
<p class="note">Source: Screener.in (BSE quarterly filings). Shows % of company held by each MF scheme.</p>
<div style="overflow-x:auto">
<table style="font-size:0.82rem">
<thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Scheme Name</th>{% for q in dii_q[:8] %}<th class="r">{{ q }}</th>{% endfor %}</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for entity in dii %}
<tr>
<td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
<td>{% if entity.url %}<a href="https://www.screener.in{{ entity.url }}" target="_blank" style="color:var(--blue)">{{ entity.name }}</a>{% else %}{{ entity.name }}{% endif %}</td>
{% for q in dii_q[:8] %}
<td class="r">{% if entity.quarters[q] is defined %}{{ "%.2f"|format(entity.quarters[q]) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
{% endfor %}
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# --- FII detail table (hidden by default) --- #}
{% if screener_shareholders and screener_shareholders.fii %}
{% set fii = screener_shareholders.fii %}
{% set fii_q = screener_shareholders.fii_quarters %}
<div id="fii-detail" style="display:none;margin-top:1rem">
<h3 style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--cyan);margin-bottom:0.5rem">Foreign Institutional Investors — {{ fii|length }} Funds</h3>
<p class="note">Source: Screener.in (BSE quarterly filings). Shows % of company held by each FII.</p>
<div style="overflow-x:auto">
<table style="font-size:0.82rem">
<thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Fund Name</th>{% for q in fii_q[:8] %}<th class="r">{{ q }}</th>{% endfor %}</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for entity in fii %}
<tr>
<td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
<td>{% if entity.url %}<a href="https://www.screener.in{{ entity.url }}" target="_blank" style="color:var(--blue)">{{ entity.name }}</a>{% else %}{{ entity.name }}{% endif %}</td>
{% for q in fii_q[:8] %}
<td class="r">{% if entity.quarters[q] is defined %}{{ "%.2f"|format(entity.quarters[q]) }}%{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
{% endfor %}
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{% if not (screener_shareholders and screener_shareholders.dii) and mf_holdings %}
{# Fallback: AMFI-sourced MF holdings if no Screener data #}
<div id="dii-detail" style="margin-top:1rem">
<h3 style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--cyan);margin-bottom:0.5rem">Mutual Fund Scheme Holdings — Top {{ mf_holdings|length }} Schemes</h3>
<p class="note">Source: AMFI monthly portfolio disclosures.</p>
<table style="font-size:0.82rem">
<thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Scheme Name</th><th>AMC</th><th class="r">Qty (shares)</th><th class="r">Value (₹Cr)</th><th class="r">% of NAV</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for h in mf_holdings[:20] %}
<tr><td>{{ loop.index }}</td><td>{{ h.scheme }}</td><td>{{ h.amc }}</td><td class="r">{{ "{:,.0f}".format(h.qty) }}</td><td class="r">{{ "{:,.1f}".format(h.value_cr) }}</td><td class="r">{{ "%.2f"|format(h.pct_nav) }}%</td></tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
{% endif %}

<div class="explain" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
<strong>What to watch:</strong> Rising FII + MF = institutional conviction is building. Falling promoter below 50% may signal dilution. Increasing public = retail interest (can be late-cycle). DIIs+ and FIIs+ show individual scheme/fund level detail — click to expand.
</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{# ============ SECTION 19: DOCUMENTS — CONCALL & ANNUAL REPORT LINKS ============ #}
{% if document_links and (document_links.concalls or document_links.annual_reports) %}
<div class="grid" style="margin-bottom:2rem">

{% if document_links.concalls %}
<div class="card">
<h2>Concall Transcripts & Presentations</h2>
<p class="note">Source: Screener.in (compiled from BSE filings). Click to open PDFs or recordings directly.</p>
<table style="font-size:0.82rem">
<thead><tr><th>Quarter</th><th>Transcript</th><th>PPT</th><th>Recording</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for cc in document_links.concalls %}
<tr>
<td><strong>{{ cc.quarter }}</strong></td>
<td>{% if cc.transcript_url %}<a href="{{ cc.transcript_url }}" target="_blank" style="color:var(--blue)">PDF</a>{% else %}<span style="color:var(--dim)">—</span>{% endif %}</td>
<td>{% if cc.ppt_url %}<a href="{{ cc.ppt_url }}" target="_blank" style="color:var(--blue)">PDF</a>{% else %}<span style="color:var(--dim)">—</span>{% endif %}</td>
<td>{% if cc.recording_url %}<a href="{{ cc.recording_url }}" target="_blank" style="color:var(--blue)">Video</a>{% else %}<span style="color:var(--dim)">—</span>{% endif %}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="explain" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
<strong>What are concall transcripts?</strong> After every quarterly result, the management holds a "conference call" with analysts. The transcript is a word-by-word record of what was said — the best source for understanding management's strategy, challenges, and forward guidance.
</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{% if document_links.annual_reports %}
<div class="card">
<h2>Annual Reports</h2>
<p class="note">Source: BSE filings via Screener.in. Full annual reports filed with the exchange.</p>
<table style="font-size:0.82rem">
<thead><tr><th>Year</th><th>Report</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for ar in document_links.annual_reports %}
<tr>
<td><strong>{{ ar.year }}</strong></td>
<td><a href="{{ ar.url }}" target="_blank" style="color:var(--blue)">Download PDF</a></td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="explain" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
